This paper deals with the formal logic and decision procedures for temporal properties, which suggests it could belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity of satisfiability and model checking problems, which could also place it in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The use of automata theory and semantics also suggests it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also deals with formal verification, which could place it in the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the correctness of decision procedures, which could also place it in the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
